cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM

This paper is about real-time semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel module and network architecture, which involves designing and optimizing the model. This suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the increasing demand for autonomous systems and robots, indicating that it could be relevant to cs.RO (Robotics and Control). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on two datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
